supportDesc.foliation:
Foliation in the top right corner of every recto page giving the total number of 187 folios. Older foliation in the top right corner of every tenth recto page giving the total number of 190 folios, which is incorrect. This is due to a miscalculation in the intervals
.

binding.condition: Damage from worms on the first and last folia.

provenance.p:

acquisition.p: The manuscript was probably acquired by Jacob Jonas Björnståhl and came to Uppsala University Library in as part of a donation by consisting of 13 Greek manuscripts.

collation.p: F. 177, which is sewn to a guard, has been misplaced. The Correct order is: 1-176, 178-184, 177, 185-187.

handDesc.handNote: The script is similar to the so-called Fettaugenmode.

origin.p: 13th or early 14th c. (before 1313). This manuscripts most likely was the exemplar of Parisinus suppl. gr. 462 which is dated to 1313.
